 production ($\\gamma\\gamma$) and...","doi":"10.17182/hepdata.150677.v1/t15","id":1639613,"location":"Data from Figure 6 located on page 11.","messages":false,"name":"Fig. 6 Mgg EBEE","processed_name":"Fig.6MggEBEE","resources":[{"description":"Original .C file","type":"C++","url":"https://www.hepdata.net/record/resource/3582518?landing_page=true"},{"description":"Image file","type":"png","url":"https://www.hepdata.net/record/resource/3582519?landing_page=true"},{"description":"Thumbnail image file","type":"png","url":"https://www.hepdata.net/record/resource/3582520?landing_page=true"}]},{"data":{"csv":"https://www.hepdata.net/download/table/ins2787227/Fig. 7 CWk limits/csv","json":"https://www.hepdata.net/download/table/ins2787227/Fig. 7 CWk limits/json","root":"https://www.hepdata.net/download/table/ins2787227/Fig. 7 CWk limits/root","yaml":"https://www.hepdata.net/download/table/ins2787227/Fig. 7 CWk limits/yaml","yoda":"https://www.hepdata.net/download/table/ins2787227/Fig. 7 CWk limits/yoda","yoda.h5":"https://www.hepdata.net/download/table/ins2787227/Fig. 7 CWk limits/yoda.h5","yoda1":"https://www.hepdata.net/download/table/ins2787227/Fig. 7 CWk limits/yoda1"},"description":"Figure 7. The exclusion limit for the clockwork framework over the k--M5 parameter space. The shaded region denotes where the...","doi":"10.17182/hepdata.150677.v1/t16","id":1639614,"location":"Data from Figure 7 located on page 12.","messages":false,"name":"Fig. 7 CWk limits","processed_name":"Fig.7CWklimits","resources":[{"description":"Original .C file","type":"C++","url":"https://www.hepdata.net/record/resource/3582522?landing_page=true"},{"description":"Image file","type":"png","url":"https://www.hepdata.net/record/resource/3582523?landing_page=true"},{"description":"Thumbnail image file","type":"png","url":"https://www.hepdata.net/record/resource/3582524?landing_page=true"}]}],"mode":"record","overall_status":"finished","participant_count":3,"recid":150677,"record":{"abstract":"Results are presented from a search for new physics in high-mass diphoton events from proton-proton collisions at $\\sqrt{s}$ = 13 TeV. The data set was collected in 2016-2018 with the CMS detector at the LHC and corresponds to an integrated luminosity of 138 fb$^{-1}$. Events with a diphoton invariant mass greater than 500 GeV are considered. Two different techniques are used to predict the standard model backgrounds: parametric fits to the smoothly-falling background and a first-principles calculation of the standard model diphoton spectrum at next-to-next-to-leading order in perturbative quantum chromodynamics calculations. The first technique is sensitive to resonant excesses while the second technique can identify broad differences in the invariant mass shape. The data are used to constrain the production of heavy Higgs bosons, Randall-Sundrum gravitons, the large extra dimensions model of Arkani-Hamed, Dimopoulos, and Dvali (ADD), and the continuum clockwork mechanism. No statistically significant excess is observed. The present results are the strongest limits to date on ADD extra dimensions and RS gravitons with a coupling parameter greater than 0.1.","access_urls":{"links":{"csv":"https://www.hepdata.net/download/submission/ins2787227/1/csv","json":"https://www.hepdata.net/download/submission/ins2787227/1/json","root":"https://www.hepdata.net/download/submission/ins2787227/1/root","yaml":"https://www.hepdata.net/download/submission/ins2787227/1/yaml","yoda":"https://www.hepdata.net/download/submission/ins2787227/1/yoda"}},"analyses":[],"arxiv_id":"arXiv:2405.09320","collaborations":["CMS"],"control_number":"150677","creation_date":"2024-05-15","data_abstract":"","data_keywords":{"cmenergies":[]},"doc_type":"publication","doi":"10.1007/JHEP08(2024)215","first_author":{"affiliation":"Yerevan Phys. Inst.","full_name":"Hayrapetyan, Aram"},"hepdata_doi":"10.17182/hepdata.150677.v1","id":150677,"inspire_id":"2787227","journal_info":"JHEP 08 (2024) 215","keywords":[{"